{109}{}{这是一个很好的。回头见。 -- That's a good one. See you later.}
### {110}{}{Sure, I will be glad to help.}
{110}{}{当然，我很乐意帮忙。 -- Sure, I will be glad to help.}
### {111}{}{Of course. Ask around, most of these people are workers and traders so I'm sure you'll find anything you need.}
{111}{}{当然问问周围，这些人大多是工人和贸易商，所以我相信你会找到你需要的任何东西。 -- Of course. Ask around, most of these people are workers and traders so I'm sure you'll find anything you need.}
### {112}{}{Alright. I'll do that.}
{112}{}{好吧我会那样做的。 -- Alright. I'll do that.}
### {113}{}{[Looking at his files.] I think I have something for you. One of the locals is having problems with his brahmin. He claims that they refuse to eat and started behaving weird. He is suspecting that someone is trying to poison his brahmin but he couldn't find any proof in the water or their food.}
{113}{}{[看他的档案。]我想我有东西要给你。一个当地人对他的婆罗门有意见。他声称他们拒绝进食并开始表现怪异。他怀疑有人试图毒害他的婆罗门，但他在水中或他们的食物中找不到任何证据。 -- [Looking at his files.] I think I have something for you. One of the locals is having problems with his brahmin. He claims that they refuse to eat and started behaving weird. He is suspecting that someone is trying to poison his brahmin but he couldn't find any proof in the water or their food.}
### {114}{}{So, any other possible cause?}
{114}{}{那么，还有其他可能的原因吗？ -- So, any other possible cause?}
### {115}{}{It could be wild dogs, rats... who knows. After all, I can't blame the man for being overly worried. He invested all his money into this. I promised I would check it out but I'm pretty busy around here so I trust you will help if you can, right?}
{115}{}{可能是野狗、老鼠。。。谁知道呢。毕竟，我不能责怪这个男人过于担心。他把所有的钱都投入到这件事上。我答应过我会去看看，但我在这里很忙，所以如果可以的话，我相信你会帮忙的，对吧？ -- It could be wild dogs, rats... who knows. After all, I can't blame the man for being overly worried. He invested all his money into this. I promised I would check it out but I'm pretty busy around here so I trust you will help if you can, right?}
### {116}{}{Sure, do I get something for this?}
{116}{}{当然，我要买点什么吗？ -- Sure, do I get something for this?}
### {117}{}{Sorry, I have something else to do right now.}
{117}{}{对不起，我现在还有别的事要做。 -- Sorry, I have something else to do right now.}
### {118}{}{Well, you can always use some more money, I guess. Listen, I don't expect this to be some wild-goose chase so I can give you $500 for the job.}
{118}{}{嗯，我想你总是可以用更多的钱。听着，我不希望这是一场徒劳的追逐，所以我可以给你500美元来做这份工作。 -- Well, you can always use some more money, I guess. Listen, I don't expect this to be some wild-goose chase so I can give you $500 for the job.}
### {119}{}{Fair enough. Tell me what has to be done?}
{119}{}{很公平。告诉我该怎么办？ -- Fair enough. Tell me what has to be done?}
### {120}{}{Have a nice day, Jerry.}
{120}{}{祝你今天愉快，杰瑞。 -- Have a nice day, Jerry.}
### {121}{}{Alright, his small farm is just east of here. I suspect if anything is happening there, it has to be during the night. So if you head there after sunset you can get a better clue of what's going on.}
{121}{}{好吧，他的小农场就在这里的东边。我怀疑如果那里发生了什么事，那一定是在晚上。因此，如果你在日落后前往那里，你可以更好地了解发生了什么。 -- Alright, his small farm is just east of here. I suspect if anything is happening there, it has to be during the night. So if you head there after sunset you can get a better clue of what's going on.}
### {122}{}{I'm on it.}
{122}{}{我在上面。 -- I'm on it.}
